"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-how-super-falcons-can-qualify-after-defeats-to-brazil-spain\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Super Falcons still have a chance of qualifying for the knockout stages of the football event at the ongoing Olympic Games in Paris, France.  Nigeria suffered their second consecutive defeat in the group stage to Spain on Sunday.  In their first fixture, they lost 1-0 to Brazil, with veteran Marta grabbing the only goal.  The Falcons also suffered another narrow loss to Spain, with Putellas clinching the winner with a direct free goal.  Randy Waldrum's ladies are now rooted to the bottom of Group C with zero points.  Nigeria are now condemned to beat Japan in their final group game, to stand a chance of qualifying to the next stage as one of the best losers in the football event.  EPL: He's the best ever - Toby Collyer hails Man United star  Transfer: Why I signed Varane after he left Man Utd - Fabregas  Israel-US war in Iran illegal, causing damage to civilians - Spain's PM Sanchez  'I am upset, sad' - Neymar reacts after being dropped by Ancelotti from Brazil's squad  Real reason I did not include Neymar in Brazil squad - Ancelotti  Spain's PM Sanchez urges end to UN Security Council veto power, blasts US for global conflicts  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"